Note:
Windows x86_64 NT System Call Definitions

Defines NT kernel syscall numbers, platform metadata, and registration logic
for Windows running on x86_64 processors.

CRITICAL: Windows NT syscall numbers are NOT stable across OS versions.
Microsoft does not guarantee ABI stability for NT syscalls. The numbers
defined here are for Windows 10 21H2+ and Windows 11 (build 19044+).
Applications should normally use the Win32 API (kernel32.dll, ntdll.dll)
rather than direct syscalls. Direct syscalls are used here for:
1. Minimal runtime bootstrapping before DLL loading is available
2. Security-sensitive operations that need to avoid API hooking
3. Compiler runtime initialization

Syscall convention (Windows x86_64):
- Syscall number in RAX (EAX)
- First argument: move RCX to R10 (RCX is clobbered by syscall instruction)
- Remaining arguments in RDX, R8, R9
- Additional arguments on the stack (shadow space + stack args)
- 32 bytes of shadow space must be reserved on the stack
- Return value in RAX (NTSTATUS)
- Invoked via: syscall instruction

Reference: Windows Internals, ntoskrnl.exe system service table
           Syscall numbers from Windows 10 21H2 / Windows 11 (build 19044+)
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/platform_interface.runa" as PlatformInterface
Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/syscall_registry.runa" as SyscallRegistry
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Windows x86_64 NT Syscall Number Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: These syscall numbers are for Windows 10 21H2+ and Windows 11.
Note: Numbers sourced from ntoskrnl.exe system service dispatch table.
Note: These are NOT stable across Windows versions and may change in future builds.

Note: --- Process/Thread Management ---
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_TERMINATE_PROCESS as Integer is 44        Note: 0x2C - NtTerminateProcess
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_TERMINATE_THREAD as Integer is 83         Note: 0x53 - NtTerminateThread
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_CREATE_THREAD_EX as Integer is 193        Note: 0xC1 - NtCreateThreadEx
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_OPEN_PROCESS as Integer is 38             Note: 0x26 - NtOpenProcess
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_SUSPEND_THREAD as Integer is 432          Note: 0x1B0 - NtSuspendThread (approx)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_RESUME_THREAD as Integer is 82            Note: 0x52 - NtResumeThread
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_INFORMATION_PROCESS as Integer is 25 Note: 0x19 - NtQueryInformationProcess
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_SET_INFORMATION_PROCESS as Integer is 28  Note: 0x1C - NtSetInformationProcess
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_INFORMATION_THREAD as Integer is 37 Note: 0x25 - NtQueryInformationThread
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_SET_INFORMATION_THREAD as Integer is 13   Note: 0x0D - NtSetInformationThread
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_DELAY_EXECUTION as Integer is 52          Note: 0x34 - NtDelayExecution (Sleep)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_YIELD_EXECUTION as Integer is 70          Note: 0x46 - NtYieldExecution

Note: --- File Operations ---
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_CREATE_FILE as Integer is 85              Note: 0x55 - NtCreateFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_OPEN_FILE as Integer is 51                Note: 0x33 - NtOpenFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_READ_FILE as Integer is 6                 Note: 0x06 - NtReadFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_WRITE_FILE as Integer is 8                Note: 0x08 - NtWriteFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_CLOSE as Integer is 15                    Note: 0x0F - NtClose
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_DELETE_FILE as Integer is 101             Note: 0x65 - NtDeleteFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_INFORMATION_FILE as Integer is 17   Note: 0x11 - NtQueryInformationFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_SET_INFORMATION_FILE as Integer is 39     Note: 0x27 - NtSetInformationFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_DIRECTORY_FILE as Integer is 53     Note: 0x35 - NtQueryDirectoryFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_FLUSH_BUFFERS_FILE as Integer is 75       Note: 0x4B - NtFlushBuffersFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_VOLUME_INFORMATION_FILE as Integer is 73 Note: 0x49 - NtQueryVolumeInformationFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_LOCK_FILE as Integer is 261               Note: 0x105 - NtLockFile (approx)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_UNLOCK_FILE as Integer is 263             Note: 0x107 - NtUnlockFile (approx)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_DEVICE_IO_CONTROL_FILE as Integer is 7    Note: 0x07 - NtDeviceIoControlFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_FS_CONTROL_FILE as Integer is 57          Note: 0x39 - NtFsControlFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_CREATE_NAMED_PIPE_FILE as Integer is 164  Note: 0xA4 - NtCreateNamedPipeFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_ATTRIBUTES_FILE as Integer is 61    Note: 0x3D - NtQueryAttributesFile
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_FULL_ATTRIBUTES_FILE as Integer is 62 Note: 0x3E - NtQueryFullAttributesFile

Note: --- Memory Management ---
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_ALLOCATE_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 24  Note: 0x18 - NtAllocateVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_FREE_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 30      Note: 0x1E - NtFreeVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_PROTECT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 80   Note: 0x50 - NtProtectVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 35     Note: 0x23 - NtQueryVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_READ_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 63      Note: 0x3F - NtReadVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_WRITE_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 58     Note: 0x3A - NtWriteVirtualMemory
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_FLUSH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 184    Note: 0xB8 - NtFlushVirtualMemory (approx)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_LOCK_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 260     Note: 0x104 - NtLockVirtualMemory (approx)
Constant SYS_WIN64_NT_UNLOCK_VIRTUAL_MEMORY as Integer is 262   Note: 0x106 - NtUnlockVirtualMemory (approx)

