Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fast Name-to-Number Lookup
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_windows_x86_64_syscall_number" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the NT syscall number for a given name on Windows x86_64
    Note: Numbers are for Windows 10 21H2+ / Windows 11 (build 19044+)
    Note: Returns -1 if the syscall name is not recognized

    If name is "NtCreateFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_CREATE_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtOpenFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_OPEN_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtReadFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_READ_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtWriteFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_WRITE_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtClose":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_CLOSE
    End If
    If name is "NtDeleteFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_DELETE_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtQueryInformationFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_QUERY_INFORMATION_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtSetInformationFile":
        Return SYS_WIN64_NT_SET_INFORMATION_FILE
    End If
    If name is "NtQueryDirectoryFile":
